Title: HaluEval
Authors:Junyi Li, Xiaoxue Cheng, Xin Zhao, Jian-Yun Nie, and Ji-Rong Wen

Year: 2023

Summary:
It was a reaseach on LLMs like gpt ,claude and some local models too where models were asked to give hallcinated answers of diffrent types of tasks mainly QA ,
text summrization,dilogue. It was noticed that the sensitive fields topic was the fields in which LLMs got halucinated mostly. There was also noticed that the models
were getting more accurate after providing the required information for the questions. Small models like alpaca, Falcon, llama2 were getting hallucinated most,each 
was of 7B.From the paper we can easily see how much risky it is to use LLMs for real application tasks , we first need a verification of facts and information beofre 
using it into real world.

Method:
This experiment employed Chatgpt to generate diffrent questions for other models with an some info provided before ,and correct answer and halucinated answer then 
got responses from different models 

